President Trump met with Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman of Saudi Arabia at the Imperial Hotel in Osaka, Japan. Trump praised the Crown Prince for his efforts in opening up Saudi Arabia and improving the rights of women. They discussed trade, economic development, and military cooperation between the two countries. Trump commended Saudi Arabia for its fight against terrorism and its efforts to cut off funding to terrorist groups. The President also mentioned his potential meeting with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un at the DMZ during his upcoming visit to South Korea. He expressed optimism about the relationship between the US and China, as he prepared to meet with Chinese President Xi Jinping to discuss trade and Huawei.